The Inventory Auditor"
You are managing a warehouse database. You need to compare incoming shipment data against the warehouse standards.

The Variables:

Python
item_count = "50"        # Note: This is a string
storage_capacity = 100
current_stock = 45.0     # Note: This is a float
restricted_items = ["Chemicals", "Electronics", "Perishables"]
new_item = "Electronics"

Your Challenge:
Write the Python expressions for the following (using print() to see the result):
The Type Trap: Check if item_count is equal to 50. (Hint: Pay attention to the data types!)
The Comparison: Check if current_stock is less than or equal to storage_capacity.
The Membership Test: Check if new_item is "in" the restricted_items list.
The Identity Check: Check if the type of item_count is NOT the same as the type of storage_capacity.
The Threshold: Check if current_stock plus int(item_count) exceeds the storage_capacity.

print(item_count == "50")
print(current_stock <= storage_capacity)
print(new_item in restricted_items)
print(type(item_count) != (storage_capacity))
print(current_stock + int(item_count) > storage_capacity)


